ODM party leader Raila Odinga today held talks with ambassadors and heads of missions from the European Union, the united states and the united nations a year to the next general election. During the 2 hours closed-door meeting attended by ODM party officials Junet Mohammed and Opiyo Wandayi, it is said that the ODM party leader was encouraged by the sentiments of the ambassadors on their plans to boost the economy and cushion Kenyans from the biting economic times. The ambassadors also sought assurances that the campaigns and election exercise will be peaceful. Meanwhile, ANC party leader Musalia Mudavadi has insisted that just like in the 2013 general polls, he is determined to go up to the ballot.